#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Build plugin allows you to run actions like build, clean and compile on "
"a project. You can also automatically run the generated applications. The "
"plugin basically gives you a way to configure sets of commands to run and it "
"can parse the output for links to files and specific lines and columns in "
"those files. So even if the plugin is originally created for compiling C/C++ "
"and mostly tested with it, the plugin can also be useful for other purposes "
"and languages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Build Plugin"
msgstr "Build Plugin इत्यस्य उपयोगः"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:598
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The Build plugin adds a <guilabel>Build Output</guilabel> tool view at "
#| "the bottom and a <guimenu>Build</guimenu> menu on the menubar. The tool "
#| "view can be used to configure build target settings, while the menu can "
#| "be used to perform build, clean and compile actions."
msgid ""
"The Build plugin adds a <guilabel>Build</guilabel> tool view at the bottom "
"and a <guimenu>Build</guimenu> menu on the menu bar. The tool view can be "
"used to select and configure build targets, while the menu and its shortcuts "
"can be used to select and execute the configured shell commands."
msgstr ""
"Build प्लगिन् अधः <guilabel>Build Output</guilabel> इति साधनदृश्यं तथा च "
"मेनूपट्टिकायां <guimenu>Build</guimenu> मेन्यू योजयति । tool view इत्यस्य उपयोगः "
"build target settings इत्यस्य विन्यासार्थं कर्तुं शक्यते, यदा तु menu इत्यस्य उपयोगः "
"build, clean, compile क्रियाः कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

