#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2673
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that each \"command\" may be an array or a string (in which case it is "
"split into an array). Also, a top-level \"global\" entry (next to \"server"
"\") is considered as well (see further below). The specified binary is "
"searched for in the usual way, e.g. using <literal>PATH</literal>. If it is "
"installed in some custom location, then the latter may have to be extended. "
"Or alternatively, a (sym)link or wrapper script may be used in a location "
"that is within the usual <literal>PATH</literal>. As illustrated above, one "
"may also specify a \"path\" that will be searched for after the standard "
"locations."
msgstr ""
"ध्यानं कुर्वन्तु यत् प्रत्येकं \"आदेशः\" सरणी अथवा स्ट्रिंग् भवितुम् अर्हति (अस्मिन् सति सः "
"सरणीरूपेण विभक्तः भवति) । अपि च, शीर्षस्तरीयः \"वैश्विक\" प्रविष्टिः (\"सर्वर\" इत्यस्य "
"पार्श्वे) अपि विचार्यते (अधः अधिकं पश्यन्तु) । निर्दिष्टं द्विचक्रिका सामान्यरीत्या अन्वेष्यते, "
"यथा- <literal>PATH</literal> इत्यस्य उपयोगेन । यदि कस्मिन्चित् इष्टस्थाने संस्थापितम् "
"अस्ति तर्हि उत्तरस्य विस्तारः कर्तव्यः भवेत् । अथवा वैकल्पिकरूपेण सामान्यस्य <literal>PATH</"
"literal>-अन्तर्गतं स्थाने (sym)link अथवा wrapper स्क्रिप्ट् उपयोक्तुं शक्यते । यथा उपरि "
"दर्शितं, मानकस्थानानां अनन्तरं अन्वेष्टव्यः \"मार्गः\" अपि निर्दिष्टुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All of the entries in \"command\", \"root\" and \"path\" are subject to "
"variable expansion."
msgstr ""
"\"command\", \"root\" तथा \"path\" इत्यत्र सर्वाणि प्रविष्टयः चरविस्तारस्य अधीनाः "
"सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The \"highlightingModeRegex\" is used to map the highlighting mode as used "
"by &kate; to the language id of the server. If no regular expression is "
"given, the language id itself is used. If a \"documentLanguageId\" entry is "
"set to false, then no language id is provided to the server when opening the "
"document. This may have better results for some servers that are more "
"precise in determining the document type than doing so based on a kate mode."
msgstr ""
"\"highlightingModeRegex\" इत्यस्य उपयोगः हाइलाइटिङ्ग् मोड् इत्यस्य नक्शाङ्कनार्थं भवति "
"यथा &kate; सर्वरस्य भाषा id प्रति । यदि नियमितव्यञ्जनं न दत्तं तर्हि भाषा id एव "
"उपयुज्यते । यदि \"documentLanguageId\" प्रविष्टिः false इति सेट् भवति, तर्हि दस्तावेजं "
"उद्घाटयति समये सर्वरं प्रति कोऽपि भाषा id न प्रदत्तः । एतस्य केषाञ्चन सर्वराणां कृते "
"उत्तमाः परिणामाः भवितुम् अर्हन्ति ये kate मोड् इत्यस्य आधारेण करणस्य अपेक्षया "
"दस्तावेजप्रकारस्य निर्धारणे अधिकं सटीकाः भवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the above example, the gist is presumably clear. In addition, each "
"server entry object may also have an \"initializationOptions\" entry, which "
"is passed along to the server as part of the 'initialize' method. If "
"present, a \"settings\" entry is passed to the server by means of the "
"'workspace/didChangeConfiguration' notification. Either of "
"\"completionTriggerCharacters\" or \"signatureTriggerCharacters\" may be "
"specified as a JSON object with string members \"exclude\" and/or \"include"
"\". These will be used to respectively exclude or add some characters to the "
"respective trigger set as provided by the server."
msgstr ""
"उपर्युक्तोदाहरणात् सारः स्पष्टः इति अनुमानं भवति । तदतिरिक्तं, प्रत्येकं सर्वरप्रविष्टिवस्तु "
"\"initializationOptions\" प्रविष्टिः अपि भवितुम् अर्हति, यत् 'initialize' पद्धतेः "
"भागरूपेण सर्वरं प्रति प्रसारितं भवति । यदि वर्तते तर्हि 'workspace/"
"didChangeConfiguration' इति सूचनायाः माध्यमेन \"settings\" इति प्रविष्टिः सर्वरं "
"प्रति प्रसारिता भवति । \"completionTriggerCharacters\" अथवा "
"\"signatureTriggerCharacters\" इत्येतयोः मध्ये एकं JSON वस्तुरूपेण निर्दिष्टं भवितुम् "
"अर्हति यत्र स्ट्रिंग् सदस्यैः \"exclude\" तथा/वा \"include\" भवति एतेषां उपयोगः क्रमेण "
"सर्वरेण प्रदत्तवत् तत्तत् ट्रिगर सेट् मध्ये केचन वर्णाः बहिष्कृत्य वा योजयितुं वा भविष्यन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Various stages of override/merge are applied;"
msgstr "अधिलिखित/विलयस्य विविधाः चरणाः प्रयुक्ताः भवन्ति;"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2713
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"user configuration (loaded from file) overrides (internal) default "
"configuration"
msgstr "उपयोक्तृविन्यासः (सञ्चिकातः लोड् कृतः) (आन्तरिकं) पूर्वनिर्धारितं विन्यासं अधिलिखति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2716
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\"lspclient\" entry in <filename>.kateproject</filename> project "
"configuration overrides the above"
msgstr ""
"<filename>.kateproject</filename> परियोजनाविन्यासे \"lspclient\" प्रविष्टिः "
"उपरिष्टाद् अधिलिखति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the resulting \"global\" entry is used to supplement (not override) any "
"server entry"
msgstr ""
"परिणामी \"वैश्विक\" प्रविष्टिः कस्यापि सर्वरप्रविष्टेः पूरकत्वेन (न तु अधिलिखितुं) उपयुज्यते"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One server instance is used per (root, servertype) combination. If \"root\" "
"is specified as an absolute path, then it used as-is, otherwise it is "
"relative to the <quote>projectBase</quote> (as determined by the <link "
"linkend=\"kate-application-plugin-projects\">Project plugin</link>) if "
"applicable, or otherwise relative to the document's directory. If not "
"specified and \"rootIndicationFileNames\" is an array as filenames, then a "
"parent directory of current document containing such a file is selected. "
"Alternatively, if \"root\" is not specified and \"rootIndicationFilePatterns"
"\" is an array of file patterns, then a parent directory of the current "
"document matching the file pattern is selected. As a last fallback, the home "
"directory is selected as \"root\". For any document, the resulting \"root\" "
"then determines whether or not a separate instance is needed. If so, the "
"\"root\" is passed as rootUri/rootPath."
msgstr ""
"प्रति (मूल, सर्वरप्रकार) संयोजनं एकं सर्वर-दृष्टान्तं उपयुज्यते । यदि &quot;मूलम्&quot; "
"निरपेक्षमार्गत्वेन निर्दिष्टं तर्हि यथावत् प्रयुक्तम् अन्यथा तस्य सापेक्षम्<quote> projectBase</"
"quote> (यथा निर्धारितम्<link linkend=\"kate-application-plugin-projects\"> "
"परियोजना प्लगिन्</link> ) यदि प्रयोज्यम्, अथवा अन्यथा दस्तावेजस्य निर्देशिकायाः सापेक्षम्। "
"यदि निर्दिष्टं न भवति तथा च &quot;rootIndicationFileNames&quot; सञ्चिकानामरूपेण "
"सरणी अस्ति, तर्हि तादृशसञ्चिकायुक्तस्य वर्तमानदस्तावेजस्य मातापितृनिर्देशिका चयनिता भवति । "
"वैकल्पिकरूपेण, यदि &quot;root&quot; निर्दिष्टं नास्ति तथा च &quot;"
"rootIndicationFilePatterns&quot; सञ्चिकाप्रतिमानानाम् एकः सरणी अस्ति, तर्हि "
"सञ्चिकाप्रतिमानेन सह मेलनं कुर्वन् वर्तमानदस्तावेजस्य मातापितृनिर्देशिका चयनिता भवति अन्तिमः "
"fallback इति रूपेण, गृहनिर्देशिका &quot;root&quot; इति चयनिता भवति । कस्यचित् "
"दस्तावेजस्य कृते, ततः परिणामितः &quot;मूलः&quot; पृथक् उदाहरणस्य आवश्यकता अस्ति वा न वा "
"इति निर्धारयति । यदि एवम् अस्ति तर्हि &quot;मूलम्&quot; rootUri/rootPath इति रूपेण "
"पारितं भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2738
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In general, it is recommended to leave root unspecified, as it is not that "
"important for a server (your mileage may vary though). Fewer server "
"instances are obviously more efficient, and they also have a 'wider' view "
"than the view of many separate instances."
msgstr ""
"सामान्यतया, मूलं अनिर्दिष्टं त्यक्तुं शस्यते, यतः सर्वरस्य कृते तत् तावत् महत्त्वपूर्णं नास्ति (भवतः "
"माइलेजः तथापि भिन्नः भवितुम् अर्हति) । अल्पाः सर्वर-दृष्टान्ताः स्पष्टतया अधिक-दक्षाः "
"भवन्ति, तेषां च अनेक-पृथक्-दृष्टान्तानां दृश्यापेक्षया 'विस्तृत' दृश्यं भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, several entries are subject to variable expansion. A "
"suitable application of that combined with \"wrapper script\" approaches "
"allows for customization to a great many circumstances. For example, "
"consider a python development scenario that consists of multiple projects (e."
"g. git repos), each with its own virtualenv setup. Using the default "
"configuration, the python language server will not be aware of the virtual "
"env. However, that can be remedied with the following approach. First, the "
"following fragment can be entered in LSPClient plugin's \"User Server "
"Settings\":"
msgstr ""
"यथा उपरि उक्तं, अनेकाः प्रविष्टयः चरविस्तारस्य अधीनाः सन्ति । तस्य उपयुक्तः अनुप्रयोगः "
"\"rapper script\" इति दृष्टिकोणैः सह संयुक्तः बहुषु परिस्थितिषु अनुकूलनं कर्तुं शक्नोति । "
"उदाहरणार्थं, एकं पायथन् विकासपरिदृश्यं विचारयन्तु यस्मिन् बहुविधाः परियोजनाः (उदा. git "
"repos) सन्ति, प्रत्येकस्य स्वकीयाः virtualenv सेटअपः भवति । पूर्वनिर्धारितविन्यासस्य "
"उपयोगेन, python भाषासर्वरः आभासी env विषये अवगतः न भविष्यति । तथापि तस्य निवारणं "
"निम्नलिखितपद्धत्या कर्तुं शक्यते । प्रथमं LSPClient प्लगिन् इत्यस्य \"User Server Settings"
"\" इत्यस्मिन् निम्नलिखितखण्डं प्रविष्टुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:2755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"        \"servers\":\n"
"        {\n"
"                \"python\":\n"
"                {\n"
"                        \"command\": [\"pylsp_in_env\", \"%{Project:"
"NativePath}\"],\n"
"                        \"root\": \".\"\n"
"                }\n"
"        }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{ १.\n"
"        \"सेवकाः\" : १.\n"
"        { १.\n"
"                \"पायथन्\": १.\n"
"                { १.\n"
"                        \"आदेश\": [\"pylsp_in_env\", \"% {परियोजना: "
"देशीमार्ग}\"],\n"
"                        \"मूलं\": \"।\"\n"
"                } .\n"
"        } .\n"
"} ."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The root entry above is relative to the project directory and ensures that a "
"separate language server is started for each project, which is necessary in "
"this case as each has a distinct virtual environment."
msgstr ""
"उपरि मूलप्रविष्टिः परियोजनानिर्देशिकायाः सापेक्षं भवति तथा च प्रत्येकस्य परियोजनायाः कृते "
"पृथक् भाषासर्वरः आरब्धः इति सुनिश्चितं करोति, यत् अस्मिन् सन्दर्भे आवश्यकं यतः प्रत्येकस्य "
"विशिष्टं आभासीवातावरणं भवति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>pylsp_in_env</filename> is a small \"wrapper script\" that should "
"be placed in <literal>PATH</literal> with the following (to-be-adjusted) "
"content:"
msgstr ""
"<filename>pylsp_in_env</filename> इति लघु \"wrapper script\" अस्ति यत् "
"<literal>PATH</literal> इत्यत्र निम्नलिखित (समायोजनीयम्) सामग्रीसहितं स्थापनीयम् ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:2765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
"cd $1\n"
"# run the server (python-lsp-server) within the virtualenv\n"
"# (i.e. with virtualenv variables setup)\n"
"# so source the virtualenv\n"
"source XYZ\n"
"# server mileage or arguments may vary\n"
"exec myserver"
msgstr ""
"#!/बिन/बश\n"
"cd $1\n"
"# virtualenv इत्यस्य अन्तः सर्वरं (python-lsp-server) चालयन्तु\n"
"# (अर्थात् virtualenv चर सेटअप सह)\n"
"# अतः virtualenv स्रोतः\n"
"स्रोतः XYZ\n"
"# सर्वर माइलेज अथवा तर्काः भिन्नाः भवितुम् अर्हन्ति\n"
"exec myserver इति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2766
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is but one example of a more general pattern which may be handled a bit "
"more comfortably as outlined in the <link linkend=\"lspclient-exec"
"\">Execution environment</link> section below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:2773
#, no-c-format
msgid "LSP Server Configuration"
msgstr "LSP सर्वर विन्यासः"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each particular LSP server has its own way of customization and may use "
"language/tool specific means for configuration, &eg; <filename>tox.ini</"
"filename> (a.o. for python), <filename>.clang-format</filename> for C++ "
"style format. Such configuration may then also be used by other (non-LSP) "
"tools (such as then <application>tox</application> or <application>clang-"
"format</application>). On top of that, some LSP servers also load "
"configuration from custom files (&eg; <filename>.ccls</filename>). "
"Furthermore, custom server configuration can also be passed through LSP "
"(protocol), see the aforementioned \"initializationOptions\" and \"settings"
"\" entries in server configuration."
msgstr ""
"प्रत्येकस्य विशेषस्य LSP सर्वरस्य अनुकूलनस्य स्वकीयः मार्गः अस्ति तथा च विन्यासार्थं भाषा/"
"उपकरणविशिष्टसाधनानाम् उपयोगं कर्तुं शक्नोति, &eg; <filename>tox.ini</filename> (a."
"o. पायथन् कृते), <filename>.clang-format</filename> C++ शैलीस्वरूपस्य कृते । ततः "
"एतादृशविन्यासः अन्यैः (non-LSP) साधनैः (यथा तदा <application>tox</application> "
"अथवा <application>clang-format</application>) अपि उपयोक्तुं शक्यते । तस्य उपरि केचन "
"LSP सर्वराः अपि इष्टसञ्चिकाभ्यः (&eg; <filename>.ccls</filename>) विन्यासं लोड् "
"कुर्वन्ति । अपि च, कस्टम् सर्वर विन्यासः LSP (protocol) मार्गेण अपि पारितुं शक्यते, सर्वर "
"विन्यासे पूर्वोक्ताः \"initializationOptions\" तथा \"settings\" प्रविष्टयः पश्यन्तु ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since various level of override/merge are applied, the following example of "
"user specified client configuration tweaks some python-language-server "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"यतः ओवरराइड/विलयनस्य विविधस्तरः प्रयुक्तः भवति, उपयोक्तृनिर्दिष्टस्य क्लायन्ट् विन्यासस्य "
"निम्नलिखितम् उदाहरणं किञ्चित् python-language-server विन्यासं tweaks करोति ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:2796
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"servers\": {\n"
"        \"python\": {\n"
"            \"settings\": {\n"
"                \"pyls\": {\n"
"                    \"plugins\": {\n"
"                        \"pylint\": {\n"
"                            \"enable\": true\n"
"                        }\n"
"                    }\n"
"                }\n"
"            }\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{ १.\n"
"    \"सेवकाः\": {\n"
"        \"पायथन\": {\n"
"            \"सेटिंग्स्\": {\n"
"                \"पायल्स्\": {\n"
"                    \"प्लगिन्स्\": {\n"
"                        \"पाइलिन्ट्\": {\n"
"                            \"सक्षमम्\": सत्यम्\n"
"                        } .\n"
"                    } .\n"
"                } .\n"
"            } .\n"
"        } .\n"
"    } .\n"
"} ."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2798
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, LSP server configuration/customization is often not so well "
"documented, in ways that only examining the source code shows configuration "
"approaches and the set of available configuration options. In particular, "
"the above example's server supports many more options in \"settings\". See "
"<ulink url=\"https://github.com/neoclide/coc.nvim/wiki/Language-servers\"> "
"another LSP client's documentation</ulink> for various other language server "
"examples and corresponding settings, which can easily and readily be "
"transformed to the &JSON; configuration that is used here and outlined above."
msgstr ""
"दुर्भाग्येन, LSP सर्वर विन्यास/अनुकूलीकरणं प्रायः एतावत् सुदस्तावेजितं न भवति, एतादृशरीत्या "
"यत् केवलं स्रोतसङ्केतस्य परीक्षणेन विन्यासदृष्टिकोणाः उपलब्धविन्यासविकल्पानां समुच्चयः च दृश्यन्ते "
"विशेषतः, उपर्युक्तस्य उदाहरणस्य सर्वरः \"सेटिङ्ग्स्\" इत्यत्र अधिकानि विकल्पानि समर्थयति । "
"अन्येषां विविधानां भाषासर्वर-उदाहरणानां तत्सम्बद्धानां च सेटिङ्ग्स् कृते <ulink url="
"\"https://github.com/neoclide/coc.nvim/wiki/Language-servers\"> अन्यस्य LSP "
"क्लायन्ट्-दस्तावेजीकरणं</ulink> पश्यन्तु, ये सुलभतया सुलभतया च कर्तुं शक्नुवन्ति &JSON; "
"विन्यासः यः अत्र प्रयुक्तः उपरि उल्लिखितः च ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:2812
#, no-c-format
msgid "LSP Server Format On Save"
msgstr "LSP सर्वर प्रारूपं On Save"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2814
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can enable \"format on save\" from LSP settings in configure dialog."
msgstr "configure संवादे LSP सेटिंग्स् तः \"format on save\" सक्षमं कर्तुं शक्नुवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:2821
#, no-c-format
msgid "LSP Server Diagnostic Suppression"
msgstr "LSP सर्वर निदानदमनम्"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It may happen that diagnostics are reported which are not quite useful. This "
"can be quite cumbersome, especially if there are many (often of the same "
"kind). In some cases, this may be tweaked by language (server) specific "
"means. For example, the <ulink url=\"https://clangd.llvm.org/config.html"
"\">clangd configuration mechanism</ulink> allows tweaking of some "
"diagnostics aspects. In general, however, it may not always be evident how "
"to do so, or it may not even be possible at all in desired ways due to "
"server limitations or bug."
msgstr ""
"सम्भवति यत् निदानं निवेदितं भवति ये सर्वथा उपयोगिनो न भवन्ति। एतत् अत्यन्तं बोझिलं भवितुम् "
"अर्हति, विशेषतः यदि बहवः (प्रायः समानप्रकारस्य) सन्ति । केषुचित् सन्दर्भेषु भाषा (सर्वर) "
"विशिष्टसाधनेन एतत् tweaked भवितुम् अर्हति । यथा, <ulink url=\"https://clangd.llvm."
"org/config.html\">clangd विन्यासतन्त्रम्</ulink> केषाञ्चन निदानपक्षेषु tweaking "
"अनुमन्यते । सामान्यतया तु कथं कर्तव्यमिति सर्वदा स्पष्टं न भवति, अथवा सर्वरसीमानां कारणेन "
"अथवा दोषस्य कारणेन इष्टरीत्या सर्वथा अपि न सम्भवति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2833
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As such, the plugin supports diagnostics suppression similar to e.g. "
"valgrind suppressions. The most fine-grained configuration can be supplied "
"in a \"suppressions\" key in the (merged) &JSON; configuration."
msgstr ""
"अतः प्लगिन् निदानदमनं समर्थयति यथा उदा. वल्ग्रिन्द दमनम् । अत्यन्तं सूक्ष्मकणिकायुक्तं विन्यासं "
"(विलयित) &JSON; विन्यासः ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:2839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"servers\": {\n"
"        \"c\": {\n"
"            \"suppressions\": {\n"
"                \"rulename\": [\"filename\", \"foo\"],\n"
"                \"clang_pointer\": [\"\", \"clang-tidy\", \"clear_pointer"
"\"],\n"
"            }\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"{ १.\n"
"    \"सेवकाः\": {\n"
"        \"ग\": {\n"
"            \"दमनानि\": {\n"
"                \"नियमनाम\": [\"सञ्चिकानाम\", \"foo\"],\n"
"                \"क्लैंग_पॉइंटर\": [\"\", \"क्लैंग-टिडी\", \"क्लियर_पॉइंटर\"],\n"
"            } .\n"
"        } .\n"
"    } .\n"
"} ."

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each (valid) rule has an arbitrary name and is defined by an array of length "
"2 or 3 which provides a regex to match against the (full) filename, a regex "
"to match against the diagnostic (text) and an optional regex matched against "
"the (source code range of) text to which the diagnostic applies."
msgstr ""
"प्रत्येकं (वैधं) नियमं मनमाना नाम भवति तथा च 2 अथवा 3 दीर्घतायाः सरणीद्वारा परिभाषितं "
"भवति यत् (पूर्ण) सञ्चिकानामस्य विरुद्धं मेलयितुम् एकं regex, निदानस्य (पाठस्य) विरुद्धं "
"मेलयितुम् एकं regex तथा च विरुद्धं मेलनं कृत्वा वैकल्पिकं regex प्रदाति (source code range "
"of) पाठः यस्मिन् निदानं प्रवर्तते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2848
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition to the above fine-grained configuration, the context menu in the "
"diagnostics tab also supports add/remove of suppressions that match a "
"particular diagnostic (text) exactly, either globally (any file) or locally "
"(the specific file in question). These suppression are stored in and loaded "
"from session config."
msgstr ""
"उपर्युक्तस्य सूक्ष्म-कणिका-विन्यासस्य अतिरिक्तं, निदान-ट्याब् मध्ये सन्दर्भ-मेनू अपि दमनस्य "
"योजयितुं/निष्कासनं समर्थयति यत् कस्यचित् विशेषस्य निदानस्य (पाठस्य) सटीकरूपेण मेलनं करोति, "
"वैश्विकरूपेण (किमपि सञ्चिका) अथवा स्थानीयरूपेण (प्रश्ने विशिष्टा सञ्चिका) एते दमनाः "
"सत्रविन्यासे संगृह्यन्ते, लोड् भवन्ति च ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:2858
#, no-c-format
msgid "LSP Server Troubleshooting"
msgstr "LSP सर्वर समस्यानिवारणम्"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is one thing to describe how to configure a (custom) LSP server for any "
"particular language, it is another to end up with the server running "
"smoothly. Usually, the latter is fortunately the case. Sometimes, however, "
"problems may arise due to either some \"silly\" misconfiguration or a more "
"fundamental problem with the server itself. The latter might typically "
"manifest itself as a couple of attempts at starting the server, as so "
"reported in &kate; Output tab. The latter, however, is only meant to convey "
"high-level messages or progress rather than to provide detailed diagnostics, "
"and even less so for what is in fact another process (the LSP server)."
msgstr ""
"कस्यापि भाषाविशेषस्य कृते (कस्टम्) LSP सर्वरं कथं विन्यस्तं कर्तव्यमिति वर्णनं एकं कार्यं, सर्वरं "
"सुचारुरूपेण चालितं कृत्वा समाप्तुं अन्यत् । प्रायः उत्तरं दिष्ट्या एव भवति । परन्तु कदाचित् "
"कस्यचित् \"मूर्ख\" दुर्विन्यासस्य कारणेन अथवा सर्वरस्य एव अधिका मौलिकसमस्यायाः कारणेन "
"समस्याः उत्पद्यन्ते । उत्तरार्द्धं सामान्यतया सर्वरस्य आरम्भस्य द्वे प्रयासे प्रकटितुं शक्नोति, "
"यथा &kate; आउटपुट ट्याब्। उत्तरं तु केवलं विस्तृतनिदानं दातुं न अपितु उच्चस्तरीयसन्देशान् वा "
"प्रगतिः वा प्रसारयितुं अभिप्रेतम्, अपि च यत् वस्तुतः अन्यप्रक्रिया (LSP सर्वर) इति कृते अपि "
"न्यूनम्"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2872
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The usual way to diagnose this is to add some flag(s) to the startup command "
"(of the language server) that enables (additional) logging (to some file or "
"standard error), in as far as it does not do so by default. If &kate; is "
"then started on the command line, then one might be able to obtain more "
"(in)sight in what might be going wrong."
msgstr ""
"एतस्य निदानस्य सामान्यः उपायः अस्ति यत् प्रारम्भ-आदेशे (भाषासर्वरस्य) केचन ध्वजाः (ध्वजाः) "
"योजयितुं यत् (अतिरिक्तं) लॉगिंग् (कस्मिंश्चित् सञ्चिकायां वा मानकदोषे वा) सक्षमं करोति, "
"यथावत् पूर्वनिर्धारितरूपेण न करोति . यदि &कते; ततः आदेशपङ्क्तौ आरभ्यते, तदा किं किं भ्रष्टं "
"भवेत् इति अधिकं (अन्)दृष्टिः प्राप्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2880
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "It may also be informative to examine the protocol exchange between "
#| "&kate;'s LSP client and the LSP server. Again, the latter usually has "
#| "ways to trace that. The LSP client also provides additional debug tracing "
#| "(to stderr) when &kate; is invoked with the following "
#| "<literal>QT_LOGGING_RULES=katelspclientplugin=true</literal> suitably "
#| "<literal>export</literal>'ed."
msgid ""
"It may also be informative to examine the protocol exchange between &kate;'s "
"LSP client and the LSP server. Again, the latter usually has ways to trace "
"that. The LSP client also provides additional debug tracing (to stderr) when "
"&kate; is invoked with the following <literal>LSPCLIENT_DEBUG=1</literal> "
"suitably <literal>export</literal>'ed."
msgstr ""
"&kate;'s LSP क्लायन्ट् तथा LSP सर्वर इत्येतयोः मध्ये प्रोटोकॉल-आदान-प्रदानस्य परीक्षणं "
"अपि सूचनाप्रदं भवितुम् अर्हति । पुनः उत्तरस्य प्रायः तस्य अनुसन्धानस्य उपायाः सन्ति । LSP "
"क्लायन्ट् अतिरिक्तं त्रुटिनिवारणं (stderr कृते) अपि प्रदाति यदा &kate; निम्नलिखित "
"<literal>QT_LOGGING_RULES=katelspclientplugin=true</literal> उपयुक्ततया "
"<literal>निर्यात</literal>'ed सह आह्वानं भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2894
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The python virtualenv example above is but one example of an \"execution "
"environment\" that operates in a distinct and separate way from the usual "
"host environment. This could be achieved by different variable settings (e."
"g. virtualenv), or a (s)chroot setup (switching to another dir as new root), "
"a container (e.g. podman, docker), or an ssh session to another host. In "
"each case, the \"other environment\" is defined by an \"execution prefix\". "
"That is, some program can be invoked/run in the other environment by means "
"of a \"prefix\" (a program and arguments) appended with the intended "
"invocation. For example, <literal>podman exec -i containername</literal> or "
"<literal>ssh user@host</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2907
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In particular, as in the previous virtualenv example, one may choose/need to "
"run an LSP server is such a separate environment (e.g. a container with all "
"dependencies needed by some project). The \"manual\" approach outlined above "
"has as disadvantage that it replaces the standard LSP command-line, which "
"then has to specified and duplicated again in the wrapper script. Also, in "
"some of the other examples mentioned above the \"path namespace\" of host "
"(as viewed by the editor) may be different from that of the environment. To "
"address these matters in a more systematic way (than a \"custom\" approach), "
"some additional configuration can be specified."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2919
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, the following can be specified in a <literal>.kateproject</"
"literal> configuration. Obviously, the \"fake\" comments should not be "
"included."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:2924
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    // this may also be an array of objects\n"
"    \"exec\": {\n"
"        \"hostname\": \"foobar\"\n"
"        // the command could also be an array of string\n"
"        \"prefix\": \"podman exec -i foobarcontainer\",\n"
"        \"mapRemoteRoot\": true,\n"
"        \"pathMappings\": [\n"
"            // either of the following forms are possible\n"
"            // a more automagic alternative exists as well, see later/below\n"
"            [ \"/dir/on/host\", \"/mounted/in/container\" ]\n"
"            { \"localRoot\": \"/local/dir\", \"remoteRoot\": \"/remote/dir"
"\" }\n"
"        ]\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"lspclient\": {\n"
"        \"servers\": {\n"
"            \"python\": {\n"
"                // this will match/join with the above object\n"
"                \"exec\": { \"hostname\": \"foobar\" },\n"
"                // confine this server to this project root,\n"
"                // so it is not used for other projects that may be opened\n"
"                // (other servers may already employ specific roots, but "
"python generally not)\n"
"                \"root\": \".\"\n"
"            },\n"
"            \"c\": {\n"
"                // as above\n"
"                \"exec\": { \"hostname\": \"foobar\" },\n"
"                \"root\": \".\"\n"
"            }\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2926
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So, what happens as a result of the above? As mentioned, the "
"<literal>lspclient</literal> part of the above is merged onto the global "
"config, hence an <literal>exec</literal> section is found (for specified "
"languages). A search is performed for another object (that specifies "
"matching <literal>hostname</literal>) in either <literal>exec</literal> or "
"<literal>lspclient</literal> section, and a matching one is as a basis for a "
"merge. As a result, an LSP server (for C and python) will have its "
"commandline appended to the specified (variable substituted) prefix, and "
"will therefore be started within the given container. Of course, the "
"container must have been created, in a proper started state and equipped "
"with proper LSP servers. One might have been tempted to use the "
"<literal>global</literal> section (within <literal>lspclient</literal>.) "
"That could also work, but then <emphasis>all</emphasis> LSP servers would be "
"started with that prefix, including those for e.g. Markdown, Bash script or "
"JSON. It is more likely that the usual host will still supply these (if in "
"use). So, as always, it depends on your particular setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2945
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, the LSP server may now observe different (remote) paths than the "
"(local) ones that are seen and used by the editor. The specified "
"<literal>pathMappings</literal> are used to translate back and forth between "
"either within the communication with the LSP server. That is, of course, as "
"much as possible. Clearly, not all local paths have a remote representation, "
"but the missing ones are also not seen (by the server) and do not pose a "
"problem. Conversely, however, the (remote) server may now see and provide "
"references in the \"remote root\" which are not evidently/easily represented "
"in the local system. The enabled <literal>mapRemoteRoot</literal> implicitly "
"maps the remote root onto a \"local URL\" <literal>exec://foobar/</literal>, "
"which is then handled by a plain-and-simple KIO protocol. The latter "
"essentially uses (e.g.) <literal>podman exec -i foobarcontainer cat somefile"
"\"</literal> for copy from remote to local (and other such variations using "
"tools from the <literal>coreutils</literal> suite). Suffice it to say it is "
"not meant for general use and claims no performance whatsoever, but it does "
"suffice to get a referenced file quickly and easily loaded into editor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2964
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is now easily seen that a simplified version of above configuration "
"(without <literal>hostname</literal> or <literal>pathMappings</literal>) "
"could be used to handle the virtualenv without having to duplicate server "
"commandline (in wrapper script)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2971
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following may not be so easily seen, so it is mentioned here explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2976
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both a <literal>hostname</literal> and the actual <literal>prefix</literal> "
"define the execution environment (the former by name, the latter by "
"content). Within an editor process instance, the same <literal>hostname</"
"literal> should not be associated with different <literal>prefix</literal>, "
"as such leads to undefined behavior (with no diagnostic required)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2985
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both <literal>prefix</literal> and <literal>pathMappings</literal> are "
"subject to (editor) variable expansion (but do mind the foregoing item)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:2991
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At runtime, some environment variables are also set, which may be used to "
"(subtly) adjust the \"prefix launcher\"'s behavior (though again mind the "
"first item). In particular, <literal>KATE_EXEC_PLUGIN</literal> is set to "
"<literal>lspclient</literal> and <literal>KATE_EXEC_SERVER</literal> is set "
"to the server's id (e.g. <literal>python</literal>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3000
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In particular, also <literal>KATE_EXEC_INSPECT</literal> is set to "
"<literal>1</literal>. This notifies the \"prefix launcher\" that the "
"receiver (Kate plugin) accepts some out-of-band/protocol data. This allows "
"the launcher to use some means to determine path mappings (e.g. "
"<literal>podman inspect</literal>) and to communicate this in suitable "
"format. This will then be removed from the otherwise LSP protocol conforming "
"stream and used to extend any defined path mapping. This may serve as an "
"alternative to specifying e.g. bind mounts explicitly (again, duplicating "
"the container's definition). Concretely, the above snippet could then be "
"used instead;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: plugins.docbook:3010
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    // ...\n"
"    \"exec\": {\n"
"        \"hostname\": \"foobar\"\n"
"        // unfortunate repetition of name, but the helper script is plain-"
"and-simple\n"
"        \"prefix\": \"exec_inspect.sh foobarcontainer podman exec -i "
"foobarcontainer\",\n"
"        \"mapRemoteRoot\": true,\n"
"        \"pathMappings\": []\n"
"    }\n"
"    // ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Last but not least, what if the \"fallback KIO\" approach is not considered "
"adequate? It is in practice often possible to \"mount\" the remote root into "
"the local filesystem and then specify the latter in a <literal>pathMappings</"
"literal>. For starters, the well-known <literal>sshfs</literal> (fuse) "
"filesystem can mount a (really) remote system into the local one. For a "
"container (podman/docker), most (filesystem driver) setups support the "
"following trick; <screen>\n"
"$ rootdir=/proc/`podman inspect --format '{{.State.Pid}}' containername`/"
"root\n"
"# some symlinks may cause issues, see also alternative below\n"
"$ sudo mount --bind $rootdir /somewhere/containername\n"
"</screen> If that fails, then one could resort to <literal>sshfs</literal>, "
"or in fact a subset thereof to mount the remote/container root; <screen>\n"
"# see respective man-pages; sftp-server suffices for actual (unencrypted) "
"file ops protocol\n"
"$ socat 'exec:podman exec -i containername /usr/lib/openssh/sftp-server'\n"
"   'exec:sshfs -o transform_symlinks -o passive \\:/ /somewhere/"
"containername'\n"
"# ...\n"
"$ fusermount -u /somewhere/containername\n"
"</screen> Note that such mount of remote root into host filesystem is likely "
"to be specified manually and explicitly in a <literal>pathMappings</literal> "
"section (barring a very intelligent prefix launcher that arranges all such "
"automagically)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:3080
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search &amp; Replace"
msgstr "अन्वेषणं &amp; प्रत्याहृ"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3084
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kate;'s Search &amp; Replace plugin allows you to search for text or <ulink "
"url=\"help:/katepart/regular-expressions.html\">regular expressions</ulink> "
"in many different files at once. You can search all open files, all the "
"files in one directory and optionally its subdirectories, or in the active "
"file. You can even filter by filename, for instance searching only files "
"that end with a particular file extension."
msgstr ""
"&kate;'s अन्वेषणम् &amp; Replace प्लगिन् एकदा एव अनेकविधसञ्चिकासु पाठं वा <ulink url="
"\"help:/katepart/regular-expressions.html\">नियमितव्यञ्जनानि</ulink> अन्वेष्टुं "
"शक्नोति । भवान् सर्वाणि मुक्तसञ्चिकाः, एकस्मिन् निर्देशिकायां सर्वाणि सञ्चिकाः वैकल्पिकरूपेण "
"च तस्य उपनिर्देशिकासु, सक्रियसञ्चिकायां वा अन्वेष्टुं शक्नोति । भवान् सञ्चिकानाम्ना अपि "
"फ़िल्टर कर्तुं शक्नोति, यथा केवलं तानि सञ्चिकानि अन्वेष्टुं ये सञ्चिकाविस्तारविशेषेण समाप्ताः "
"सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:3097
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search Query"
msgstr "अन्वेषण प्रश्न"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3099
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following options are always displayed at the top of the Search in Files "
"tool view:"
msgstr ""
"Search in Files tool view इत्यस्य उपरि सर्वदा निम्नलिखितविकल्पाः प्रदर्शिताः भवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can have as many searches as you want open at the same time. Simply "
"click the new tab button at the top-left corner of the Search tool view and "
"a new results tab will open permitting you to perform another search."
msgstr ""
"भवन्तः यावन्तः अन्वेषणाः इच्छन्ति तावन्तः एकस्मिन् समये उद्घाटिताः भवितुम् अर्हन्ति । केवलं "
"Search tool view इत्यस्य उपरि-वामकोणे स्थितं new tab बटन् नुदन्तु ततः अन्यं search कर्तुं "
"अनुमतिं ददाति नूतनं results tab उद्घाट्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The button in the top right-corner of the Search in Files tool view will "
"toggle the bottom half of the tool view between displaying additional "
"options for the Search in Folder mode and the results of your search."
msgstr ""
"Search in Files tool view इत्यस्य उपरि दक्षिणकोणे स्थितं बटनं Search in Folder मोड् "
"इत्यस्य अतिरिक्तविकल्पानां प्रदर्शनस्य भवतः अन्वेषणस्य परिणामस्य च मध्ये tool view इत्यस्य "
"अधः अर्धं टॉग्ल् करिष्यति"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find"
msgstr "अन्वेषय"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is where you type in what you want to find. You may enter standard "
"text, or a regular expression if enabled."
msgstr ""
"अत्रैव भवन्तः यत् अन्वेष्टुम् इच्छन्ति तत् टङ्कयन्ति । भवान् मानकपाठं प्रविष्टुं शक्नोति, अथवा "
"सक्षमं चेत् नियमितव्यञ्जनं प्रविष्टुं शक्नोति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: plugins.docbook:3134
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Replace</guilabel> (text box)"
msgstr "<guilabel>प्रतिस्थापन</guilabel> (पाठपेटिका)"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replacement text that will be added to file(s) in place of the text in the "
"<guilabel>Find</guilabel> text box."
msgstr ""
"प्रतिस्थापनपाठः यः <guilabel>अन्वेषण</guilabel> पाठपेटिकायां पाठस्य स्थाने सञ्चिका(षु) "
"योजितः भविष्यति ।"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: plugins.docbook:3142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search"
msgstr "अन्वेषण"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3143
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When you've finished configuring everything, just press the "
#| "<guibutton>Search</guibutton> button to perform your search. You may also "
#| "press &Enter; in the <guilabel>Find</guilabel> text box to do the same."
msgid ""
"When you've finished configuring everything, just press the "
"<guibutton>Search</guibutton> button to perform your search; to perform the "
"search in a new tab press and hold &Ctrl; before pressing the "
"<guibutton>Search</guibutton> button. You may also press &Enter; in the "
"<guilabel>Find</guilabel> text box to do the same (similarly pressing "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Enter;</keycombo> will perform the search "
"in a new tab)."
msgstr ""
"यदा भवान् सर्वं विन्यस्य समाप्तवान् तदा केवलं <guibutton>अन्वेषण</guibutton> बटनं नुदन्तु "
"यत् भवतः अन्वेषणं कर्तुं शक्नोति । भवान् &Enter; तथैव कर्तुं <guilabel>Find</guilabel> "
"इति पाठपेटिकायां ।"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: plugins.docbook:3155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replace"
msgstr "प्रत्याहृ"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you've finished configuring everything, just press the "
"<guibutton>Replace</guibutton> button to replace the text entered in the "
"<guilabel>Find</guilabel> text box with that of the <guilabel>Replace</"
"guilabel> text box. You may also press &Enter; in the <guilabel>Replace</"
"guilabel> text box to do the same."
msgstr ""
"यदा भवान् सर्वं विन्यस्तं समाप्तवान् तदा केवलं <guilabel>Replace</guibutton> इति बटनं "
"नुदन्तु यत् <guilabel>Find</guilabel> पाठपेटिकायां प्रविष्टं पाठं <guilabel>Replace</"
"guilabel> पाठस्य स्थाने प्रतिस्थापयन्तु कोश। भवान् &Enter; तथैव कर्तुं "
"<guilabel>Replace</guilabel> इति पाठपेटिकायां ।"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: plugins.docbook:3166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Next"
msgstr "अग्रिम"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Go to the next match of your search query, switching files if necessary."
msgstr "भवतः अन्वेषणप्रश्नस्य अग्रिममेलनं गच्छन्तु, आवश्यके सति सञ्चिकाः परिवर्तयन्तु ।"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: plugins.docbook:3173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replace Checked"
msgstr "Replace Checked इति"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The same as <guibutton>Replace</guibutton>, but will only perform "
"replacements in files that are checked in the pane below."
msgstr ""
"<guibutton>Replace</guibutton> इत्यस्य समानम्, परन्तु केवलं तेषु सञ्चिकासु प्रतिस्थापनं "
"करिष्यति ये अधोलिखिते फलकस्य मध्ये परीक्षिताः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:3184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search in Folder Options"
msgstr "Folder Options इत्यत्र अन्वेषणं कुर्वन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These options are displayed below the aforementioned query options. If "
"search results are being displayed instead, press the "
"<guiicon><inlinemediaobject><imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"games-config-"
"options-22.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject></"
"guiicon> button to display them."
msgstr ""
"एते विकल्पाः पूर्वोक्तप्रश्नविकल्पानां अधः प्रदर्शिताः भवन्ति । यदि तस्य स्थाने "
"अन्वेषणपरिणामाः प्रदर्श्यन्ते तर्हि <guiicon><inlinemediaobject><imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"games-config-options-22.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></"
"imageobject></inlinemediaobject>< नुदन्तु तान् प्रदर्शयितुं /guiicon> बटनं कुर्वन्तु ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3194
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search in"
msgstr "अन्वेषणं कुर्वन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This has three options. Select <guilabel>Open Files</guilabel> to search all "
"files currently open in &kate;. Select <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> to search "
"inside a folder and optionally its subfolders. Select <guilabel>Current "
"File</guilabel> to search only in the active file."
msgstr ""
"अस्य त्रयः विकल्पाः सन्ति । &kate;मध्ये वर्तमानकाले उद्घाटितानि सर्वाणि सञ्चिकानि अन्वेष्टुं "
"<guilabel>सञ्चिकाः उद्घाटयन्तु</guilabel> इति चिनोतु । पुटस्य अन्तः तथा वैकल्पिकरूपेण "
"तस्य उपपुटयोः अन्वेषणार्थं <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> इति चिनोतु । केवलं "
"सक्रियसञ्चिकायां अन्वेषणार्थं <guilabel>वर्तमानसञ्चिका</guilabel> इति चिनोतु ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <guilabel>Projects</guilabel> plugin is loaded, you can also search "
"in the <guilabel>Current Project</guilabel> or in <guilabel>All Open "
"Projects</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"यदि <guilabel>Projects</guilabel> प्लगिन् लोड् अस्ति तर्हि भवान् "
"<guilabel>वर्तमानप्रकल्प</guilabel> इत्यत्र अथवा <guilabel>All Open Projects</"
"guilabel> इत्यत्र अपि अन्वेष्टुं शक्नोति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Match case"
msgstr "मेलप्रकरणम्"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restricts search results to only those that have the exact same combination "
"of upper and lower case letters as your search query."
msgstr ""
"अन्वेषणपरिणामान् केवलं तेषु प्रतिबन्धयति येषु भवतः अन्वेषणप्रश्नस्य सदृशं बृहत्-लघु-अक्षर-संयोजनं "
"भवति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regular expressions"
msgstr "नियमितव्यञ्जना"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Permits you to use <ulink url=\"help:/katepart/regular-expressions.html"
"\">regular expressions</ulink> instead of simple text as your search query."
msgstr ""
"भवतः अन्वेषणप्रश्नरूपेण सरलपाठस्य स्थाने <ulink url=\"help:/katepart/regular-"
"expressions.html\">नियमितव्यञ्जनानि</ulink> उपयोक्तुं अनुमतिं ददाति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Expand results"
msgstr "परिणामान् विस्तारयतु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Display all the results found in each file, instead of just a list of files "
"that contain the search query."
msgstr ""
"प्रत्येकस्मिन् सञ्चिकायां प्राप्तानि सर्वाणि परिणामानि प्रदर्शयन्तु, केवलं अन्वेषणप्रश्नं "
"समाविष्टानां सञ्चिकानां सूचीं न कृत्वा ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder"
msgstr "समुच्चय"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may enter the path of the folder you wish to search. For instance, you "
"might enter <userinput>~/development/kde/kate/</userinput> if you wished to "
"search the &kate; source code. This option is only available when using "
"<guilabel>in Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"भवन्तः यस्य पुटस्य अन्वेषणं कर्तुम् इच्छन्ति तस्य मार्गं प्रविष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति । यथा, भवान् "
"<userinput>~/development/kde/kate/</userinput> इति प्रविष्टुं शक्नोति यदि भवान् "
"&kate; स्रोतसङ्केतः । एषः विकल्पः केवलं तदा एव उपलब्धः यदा <guilabel>पुट</guilabel> "
"मोड् मध्ये उपयुज्यते ।"

#. Tag: guiicon
#: plugins.docbook:3242
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open file dialog"
msgstr "सञ्चिकासंवादं उद्घाटयन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press this button to locate the folder in your desktop's folder browser. "
"This button only works when using <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"स्वस्य डेस्कटॉपस्य समुच्चय ब्राउजर् मध्ये पुटं ज्ञातुं एतत् बटन् नुदन्तु । एतत् बटन् केवलं "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं कुर्वन् कार्यं करोति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press this button to change <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> to the parent of the "
"currently selected folder. This button only works when using "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> इत्येतत् वर्तमानचयनितपुटस्य मातापितरं परिवर्तयितुं एतत् बटनं "
"नुदन्तु । एतत् बटन् केवलं <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं कुर्वन् कार्यं "
"करोति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This button will set the <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> entry to the folder in "
"which the currently open document is located. This button only works when "
"using <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"एतत् बटन् <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> इति प्रविष्टिं यस्मिन् पुटे वर्तमानं उद्घाटितं "
"दस्तावेजं स्थितम् अस्ति तस्मिन् सेट् करिष्यति । एतत् बटन् केवलं <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> "
"मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं कुर्वन् कार्यं करोति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Filter"
msgstr "फ़िल्टर"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This permits you to only search filenames that match a particular pattern. "
"For instance, to only search files written in C++, change it to <userinput>*."
"cpp</userinput>. To search only files beginning with <literal>kate</"
"literal>, change it to <userinput>kate*</userinput>. You can enter multiple "
"filters separated with a comma (<userinput>,</userinput>). This option is "
"not available when using <guilabel>Open files</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"एतेन केवलं तानि सञ्चिकानामानि अन्वेष्टुं शक्यन्ते ये विशेषप्रतिमानेन सह सङ्गताः सन्ति । यथा, "
"केवलं C++ मध्ये लिखितानि सञ्चिकानि अन्वेष्टुं, <userinput>*.cpp</userinput> इति "
"परिवर्तयन्तु । केवलं <literal>kate</literal> इत्यनेन आरभ्यमाणानि सञ्चिकानि अन्वेष्टुं "
"<userinput>kate*</userinput> इति परिवर्तयन्तु । अल्पविरामेन (<userinput>,</"
"userinput>) पृथक्कृतानि बहुविध-छिद्राणि प्रविष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति । <guilabel>Open files</"
"guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगे एषः विकल्पः उपलब्धः नास्ति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exclude"
msgstr "बहिष्कारं कुरुत"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The opposite of <guilabel>Filter</guilabel>, this prevents &kate; from "
"searching files that match the specified patterns. As with <guilabel>Filter</"
"guilabel>, you can enter multiple patterns separated with a comma "
"(<userinput>,</userinput>). This option is not available when using "
"<guilabel>Open files</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Filter</guilabel> इत्यस्य विपरीतम्, एतेन &kate; निर्दिष्टप्रतिमानैः सह "
"सङ्गतसञ्चिकानां अन्वेषणात् । <guilabel>Filter</guilabel> इत्यस्य इव, भवन्तः अल्पविरामेन "
"(<userinput>,</userinput>) पृथक्कृतानि बहुविधप्रतिमानाः प्रविष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति । "
"<guilabel>Open files</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगे एषः विकल्पः उपलब्धः नास्ति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3293
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recursive"
msgstr "पुनरावर्तनीयम्"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is enabled, &kate; will also search in all subfolders of the "
"selected folder. This option is only available when using <guilabel>Folder</"
"guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"यदि एषः विकल्पः सक्षमः अस्ति, &kate; चयनितपुटस्य सर्वेषु उपपुटेषु अपि अन्वेषणं करिष्यति । "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं कुर्वन् एव एषः विकल्पः उपलभ्यते ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include hidden"
msgstr "गुप्तं समावेशयन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is enabled, &kate; will also search in files or folders that "
"are typically hidden by your &OS;. This option is only available when using "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"यदि एषः विकल्पः सक्षमः अस्ति, &kate; सामान्यतया भवतः &OS;द्वारा गुप्ताः सञ्चिकासु "
"अथवा पुटेषु अपि अन्वेषयिष्यति । <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं कुर्वन् "
"एव एषः विकल्पः उपलभ्यते ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3311
#, no-c-format
msgid "Follow symbolic links"
msgstr "प्रतीकात्मकलिङ्कानां अनुसरणं कुर्वन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Search in Files plugin typically does not follow <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Symbolic_link\">symbolic links</ulink>. When this option "
"is enabled, the plugin will follow them instead and search inside the files "
"or folders they reference. This option is only available when using "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> mode."
msgstr ""
"सञ्चिकासु अन्वेषणं प्लगिन् सामान्यतया <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Symbolic_link\">प्रतीकात्मकलिङ्कानि</ulink> अनुसरणं न करोति । यदा एषः विकल्पः "
"सक्षमः भवति तदा प्लगिन् तेषां स्थाने अनुसरणं करिष्यति तथा च तेषां सन्दर्भितानां सञ्चिकानां "
"अथवा पुटस्य अन्तः अन्वेषणं करिष्यति । <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> मोड् इत्यस्य उपयोगं "
"कुर्वन् एव एषः विकल्पः उपलभ्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It's possible for symbolic links to reference a folder that is the parent of "
"the folder currently being searched, or other folders that contain symbolic "
"links to their parent. If there is such a link in the folder being searched "
"and this option is enabled, &kate; will repeatedly follow the link and "
"search the folder, and the search will never complete."
msgstr ""
"प्रतीकात्मकलिङ्कानां कृते सम्भवति यत् सम्प्रति अन्वेषितस्य पुटस्य मातापितरं, अथवा अन्यपुटं येषु "
"तेषां मातापितृणां प्रतीकात्मकलिङ्कानि सन्ति यदि अन्वेष्यमाणे पुटे एतादृशः लिङ्कः अस्ति तथा च "
"एषः विकल्पः सक्षमः अस्ति तर्हि &kate; पुनः पुनः लिङ्क् अनुसृत्य पुटं अन्वेषयिष्यति, अन्वेषणं च "
"कदापि पूर्णं न भविष्यति ।"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: plugins.docbook:3328
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include binary files"
msgstr "द्विचक्रीयसञ्चिकाः समाविष्टाः कुर्वन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If enabled, &kate; will also search in files that do not appear to be text "
"files."
msgstr ""
"यदि सक्षमं भवति तर्हि &kate; पाठसञ्चिकाः न दृश्यन्ते तेषु सञ्चिकासु अपि अन्वेषयिष्यति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: plugins.docbook:3339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search Results"
msgstr "अन्वेषण परिणाम"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The results of your search are displayed below the query options. If options "
"for Search in Folder mode are displayed, simply press the "
"<guiicon><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"games-config-"
"options-22.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject></"
"guiicon> button to display them. They will also automatically be displayed "
"as soon as a search is performed."
msgstr ""
"भवतः अन्वेषणस्य परिणामाः प्रश्नविकल्पानां अधः प्रदर्शिताः भवन्ति । यदि समुच्चय मोड् मध्ये "
"अन्वेषणस्य विकल्पाः प्रदर्शिताः सन्ति तर्हि केवलं "
"<guiicon><inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"games-config-"
"options-22.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></ नुदन्तु । तान् प्रदर्शयितुं "
"inlinemediaobject></guiicon> बटनं कुर्वन्तु । अन्वेषणं कृत्वा एव ते अपि स्वयमेव प्रदर्शिताः "
"भविष्यन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The search results display a list of files that contains text that matches "
"your search query, followed by the number of matches found in that file."
msgstr ""
"अन्वेषणपरिणामाः सञ्चिकानां सूचीं प्रदर्शयन्ति येषु भवतः अन्वेषणप्रश्नेन सह सङ्गतः पाठः भवति, "
"तदनन्तरं तस्मिन् सञ्चिकायां प्राप्तानां मेलानाम् संख्या भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To see a list of matches in that file, simply click the expansion arrow to "
"the left of the file name. (If you selected the <guilabel>Expand results</"
"guilabel> option, this will already be done for you.) The line number each "
"match is found on will be displayed, followed by the contents of that line, "
"with your search query indicated in bold text."
msgstr ""
"तस्मिन् सञ्चिकायां मेलसूचीं द्रष्टुं केवलं सञ्चिकानामस्य वामतः विस्तारबाणं नुदन्तु । (यदि भवान् "
"<guilabel>परिणामान् विस्तारयतु</guilabel> विकल्पं चिनोति तर्हि एतत् भवतः कृते पूर्वमेव "
"कृतम् भविष्यति ।) प्रत्येकं मेलनं यस्मिन् पङ्क्तिसङ्ख्यायां लभ्यते, तदनन्तरं तस्याः पङ्क्तिः "
"सामग्रीः, भवतां अन्वेषणप्रश्ना सूचिता च प्रदर्शिता भविष्यति गाढपाठे ।"

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open the file your result was found in, simply double-click it. &kate; "
"will open the file if needed. You can also move the cursor to the location "
"of a particular match by double-clicking on its listing instead of the file "
"name."
msgstr ""
"यस्मिन् सञ्चिकायां भवतः परिणामः प्राप्तः तत् उद्घाटयितुं केवलं तस्मिन् द्विवारं क्लिक् कुर्वन्तु । "
"&कते; आवश्यकतानुसारं सञ्चिकां उद्घाटयिष्यति। सञ्चिकानामस्य स्थाने तस्य सूचीयां द्विवारं क्लिक् "
"कृत्वा कर्सरं कस्यचित् मेलविशेषस्य स्थाने अपि स्थानान्तरयितुं शक्नुवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: plugins.docbook:3371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;<keycap>F</keycap></"
"keycombo> </shortcut> <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Search in Files</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut> <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;<keycap>F</keycap></"
"keycombo> </shortcut> <guimenu>सम्पादनं</guimenu> <guimenuitem>सञ्चिकासु अन्वेषणं</"
"guimenuitem>"

