#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3657
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Functions can access the up-to-date contents of all fields through the "
"<userinput>fields</userinput> object: use <userinput>fields.my_field</"
"userinput> or <userinput>fields[\"my_field\"]</userinput>. When using a "
"function as the default value for a field, only fields defined in the text "
"before are available."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fields can be passed as arguments to functions. The field name can be used "
"directly if it is a valid &javascript; identifier and no variable with that "
"name exists. Otherwise use the <userinput>fields</userinput> object: "
"<userinput>${func(field)}</userinput>, <userinput>${func(fields.document)}</"
"userinput>, <userinput>${func(fields[\"my field\"])}</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Function fields (e.g. <userinput>${func()}</userinput>) are re-evaluated "
"every time any field's contents are changed. However, this does not apply to "
"function calls in default values: they are only evaluated once when the "
"snippet is inserted into the document."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: plugins.docbook:3667
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For more complex scripts it may be important to understand that "
#| "<emphasis>first</emphasis>, the raw snippet is inserted into the "
#| "document, and <emphasis>then</emphasis> functions are being evaluated. E."
